       OSF/Motif User's Guide


       AAAArrrreeee YYYYoooouuuu RRRReeeeaaaaddddyyyy????

       Before you begin working through the examples, take note
       that this guide assumes the following:

          +o You have a valid login on your computer and know the
            password.

          +o The required software has been properly installed.
            This includes the X Window System, OSF/Motif, and the
            Motif Resource Editor program (mmmmrrrreeee).

          +o Your system administrator has explained how to log into
            your  computer and start the X Window System and the
            Motif Window Manager.

          +o You are familiar enough with your computer to execute
            simple commands and use a text editor.

          +o You are using the default configurations for Motif.  If
            you (or your system administrator) have customized your
            Motif environment, the appearance and behavior of your
            environment may not match the examples that follow.

          +o You have a system that uses a mouse or some other
            pointing device.



























