       You should read each chapter in a single sitting--you'll
       probably spend between 25 and 45 minutes per chapter.  Most
       importantly, as you read the text and look at the figures,
       work the examples on your own computer.

       AAAAfffftttteeeerrrr tttthhhheeee EEEExxxxaaaammmmpppplllleeeessss

       After completing Chapter 3, you will be prepared to start
       using Motif in your everyday work.  It's also likely that
       you will want to further customize your own environment.  To
       help you get started, this guide includes the following
       appendixes:

          +o Appendix A, Specifying Colors, provides a list of color
            names and briefly describes how to specify custom
            colors.

          +o Appendix B, A List of Font Names, lists the font names
            that are available for you to choose from.

          +o Appendix C, Clients That Help You Manage Windows
            describes two utility programs for the X Window System.

       Additional material about Motif is listed at the end of this
       preface. You do not need to read and understand this addi-
       tional information to use Motif effectively.







